      "sacrifices": "During a DB failover (5-30 seconds with Patroni, <1 second with Aurora), assignment requests will fail or queue. Orders placed during this window experience delayed assignment.",
      "alternatives_considered": [
        "AP with conflict resolution: Use optimistic locking and detect double-assignments after the fact, then reassign. More available but introduces operational complexity (conflict resolution logic, courier notifications for reassignment) that is disproportionate for a 2-person team.",
        "Distributed lock (Redis Redlock): Decouples lock from DB, but Redlock has known correctness issues under clock skew (see Martin Kleppmann's analysis). Adds Redis as a critical dependency. Not worth the complexity.",
        "Multi-master DB: Provides availability during node failure but makes strong consistency extremely difficult. Far too complex for a 2-person team."
