      "gains": "Single source of truth. No separate lock infrastructure. SKIP LOCKED means concurrent assignment requests don't block each other — they skip already-locked couriers and try the next candidate. Proven, well-understood semantics.",
      "sacrifices": "Coupled to PostgreSQL. Cannot trivially switch databases. Assignment throughput is bounded by DB write capacity.",
