      "reason": "The entire double-assignment prevention depends on PostgreSQL row-level locking. Migrating to a different DB would require re-engineering the core invariant enforcement. This is intentional — the consistency guarantee is the most important requirement and should be rigid."
    },
    {
      "area": "Single-assignment invariant",
      "reason": "The data model enforces one active assignment per courier at the database level (unique constraint + status check). This is the core business rule and should never be bypassed."
    }
