      "options": [
        "Option A (CP — recommended): Accept brief unavailability during failover. Orders queue and are assigned once the DB recovers. Zero double-assignments ever. Simpler architecture. Failover window with managed DB is typically <1-15 seconds.",
        "Option B (AP): Stay available during failover using optimistic assignment with post-hoc conflict detection. Requires building a conflict resolution and courier-reassignment flow. More complex, more operational burden, but no order experiences delay."
